This paper deals with auctions and mechanism design, which are topics typically studied in the game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories of computer science. The specific problem studied in the paper, set-system auctions, involves combinatorial optimization and graph theory, which are also relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
